sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Application
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Storage as PVC/Database<br/>Filesystem or 5432/3306/TCP
    participant KServe as KServe InferenceService<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>ServiceMonitor

    Note over User,Prometheus: Flow 1: TrustyAI Service Model Prediction Monitoring

    User->>KServe: POST /v1/models/model:predict<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    KServe->>TrustyAI: Payload to ModelMesh Processor<br/>HTTP/HTTPS 80-443<br/>Auth: None
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Store prediction data<br/>Filesystem or DB protocol<br/>Auth: Filesystem or DB Credentials

    Prometheus->>TrustyAI: Scrape /q/metrics<br/>HTTP/8080<br/>Auth: None

    Note over User,Prometheus: Flow 2: External User Access to TrustyAI Service

    User->>Route: GET /api/explainability<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: OAuth Redirect
    Route->>OAuth: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS (service-ca)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    OAuth->>TrustyAI: Forward authenticated request<br/>HTTP/8080<br/>Forwarded Bearer
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Retrieve data<br/>Filesystem or DB protocol
    Storage-->>TrustyAI: Data response
    TrustyAI-->>OAuth: JSON Response
    OAuth-->>Route: Encrypted response
    Route-->>User: HTTPS Response

    Note over User,Prometheus: Flow 3: LM Evaluation Job Execution

    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Kueue as Kueue<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant LMESPod as LMES Pod
    participant HF as Hugging Face Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    User->>K8sAPI: Create LMEvalJob CR<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.3<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Kueue: Workload admission<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.3<br/>Auth: Service Account
    Kueue->>K8sAPI: Schedule job<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.3
    K8sAPI->>LMESPod: Start evaluation pod
    LMESPod->>HF: Download model/dataset<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: API Token (optional)
    LMESPod->>KServe: Inference requests<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    LMESPod->>S3: Store results<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS IAM/Access Key

    Note over User,Prometheus: Flow 4: Guardrails Orchestrator Request

    participant GRoute as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant GOAuth as OAuth Proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant GOrch as Guardrails Orchestrator<br/>8032/TCP HTTPS
    participant Detector as Detector InferenceService<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Generator as Generator InferenceService<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    User->>GRoute: POST /v1/guardrails<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: OAuth Redirect
    GRoute->>GOAuth: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS (service-ca)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    GOAuth->>GOrch: Authenticated request<br/>HTTPS/8032 TLS (service-ca)<br/>Forwarded Bearer
    GOrch->>Detector: Check input safety<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Detector-->>GOrch: Detection result
    GOrch->>Generator: Generate response<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Generator-->>GOrch: Generated content
    GOrch-->>GOAuth: Filtered response
    GOAuth-->>GRoute: Encrypted response
    GRoute-->>User: HTTPS Response
